UPDATES:

- Remaining orders in the queue are nearly complete. 99% of them will be shipped by the end of the week, keep an eye out for those emails. 

- First Shell Cordovan drop will be third / fourth week of July. Three colors of Marbled Rocado. Very excited to make those, get on the email list if you don’t want to miss it!

- Will have some Archer samples on the site soon from remaining Natural Buttero. Those, and what’s up on the site right now, are all that’s left. For the foreseeable future, if it’s not on the website, it’s not available to order. 

Thank you all for the support!

Emerson in Chestnut 🍂

Lots to get done before the move. Thanks for your patience as I finish out remaining/current orders. Right on track and everything is shipping within normal lead times. If you have messaged about ordering in any color of Buttero, I’ll likely be doing ordering windows for the stock line in addition to limited releases. Im just moving away from having things open and available 24/7 so things don’t get so backed up. Learning as I go. Thank you for the support. 🙏

🚨 Tuesday @ 2 p.m. Central time. 1 p.m. early access for the email list.👇 

-Marbled Blue, Burgundy, & Pink Rocado Shell Cordovan. 
- Ready to ship, free US shipping. (No monograms)
-Emerson, Erikson, Archer, Warden, & Bookmarks. 
-More photos & details, thread colors and such, will be on the product page upon release. 

After this I’ll be moving into a new space. The made-to-order line will open up again once everything is set up and ready to go. Appreciate your patience those who have reached out about that. A lot of work prepping all these, really excited to release them. Thanks everyone!

Hey y’all ✌️
Buckle up, this is a long one. But it’s worth the read I promise! 

If you hadn’t noticed, Jacob took a step back into the shadows for a little while. Why you might ask? He’s taking his talents in another direction. But I’ll let him tell you all about it when he’s ready. With that being said, I have the opportunity to keep the Harland Handmade name alive and I couldn’t be happier. 

My name is Marcus and I figured a little introductory post was in order. A little about me:
- I live in Charleston, SC with my girlfriend and two dogs Copper and Jiggy. 
-Similar to Jacob my leather working journey started in 2020 during Covid. 
-I have been running my own leather working company for about two years now. I’m moving that business into a slightly different direction and we can chat about it if you’d like!
-I was in the Navy for ten years where I served on submarines operating electronic control systems for the nuclear reactor onboard that provided propulsion and electricity. (trust me, it sounds way cooler than it is)
-I’m a student at the College of Charleston 

You’ll be seeing and hearing a lot more from me in the future so I think that’s enough info for now. Reach out and let me know if there’s anything I can do for you in the future or if you just want to chat! 

Cheers y’all

THEN AND NOW INITIATIVE

@dsleathergoods has asked makers to post their first project remade. This is a 2 year and 7 month difference! My first wallet was made with a (very) crappy Amazon tool kit and cheap scrap leather. 

I would encourage new makers to constantly experiment in the craft and not compare yourself to others! After all, it’s your expression. Make it your own!
